        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 3:03PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 303 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Granite, or 22 miles west of North Powder, moving
north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southern Union
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
